Project # 10
Name
Retrofit
Duration
November 2012 to December 2012.
Role
Developer, Bangalore, India
Tools
web Methods 8.2 Developer, SAP Adapter, Trading Networks.
Platform
Red Hat Unix
Project Description:
The project involved fresh development of 10 interfaces. The interfaces were related to shipment, invoice and
other supply chain management related data. These interfaces converted xml (OAGIS 9.4.1) format into xml
UDM 7.x format which was eventually integrated with SAP system. Both flows i.e. inbound and outbound flows
were developed to integrate SAP system with Retrofit system. For inbound flow, the xml from Retrofit system
was received at WMS side via Trading Networks. The xml was then picked from TN, processed in IS using flow
services and data was sent to SAP via SAP IDOCS. For outbound flow, data was pushed from SAP to WMS via
SAP IDOCS. The SAP IDOC was then processed to OAGIS xml in flow service and routed to TN from where it
was picked by Retrofit system. . Once the transaction is successfully processed in WMS, we acknowledge the
Retrofit system indicating that the records are processed. Exception handling is done as per the predefined
error codes.
Responsibilities:
Creating business requirement document by taking customer requirement into consideration.
Based on the requirement created technical design document.
Developing the interfaces using flow service, creating utility services.
Involved in defect fixing and handling code change requests.
Involved in Hyper Care support
Project # 11
Name
StarLight NorthStar Integration
Duration
April 2012 to November 2012
Role
Developer, Bangalore, India
Tools
web Methods 8.2 Developer, Siebel Adapter, web Service
Platform
Red Hat Unix
Project Description:
The Project is between StarLight and NorthStar for syncing databases. StarLight is a Siebel database for
ASPAC countries which stores clinical record for its customers. NorthStar is a global Siebel database that stores
clinical records of its customers globally whenever a customer of ASPAC country creates a service request in
StarLight database. A service request is created from Starlight to North Star and the SR Number is generated
as response. The interaction between NorthStar and WMS is via Siebel adapter. The interaction between
StarLight and WMS is via webService.
As a part of integration, two interfaces had to be developed:
send a service request creation from Starlight to North Star and get back the SR Number
To get status of a service request based on SR Number.
Responsibilities:
Involved in Requirement Analysis.
Creating technical design documents.
Developing the interfaces using flow service, creating utility services
Created Unit test plan and Integration test plan documents with sample Inputs provided from client
Involved in defect fixing and handling code change requests.
Migrating integration components from one environment to other and part of the system integration
testing.
